    "instructions": [
        "In a rice cooker or pot, combine rinsed jasmine rice, coconut milk, water, salt, and 1 tsp coconut sugar. Cook according to manufacturer instructions or bringing to a boil and simmering covered for 15-18 mins. Fluff when done.",
        "While rice cooks, mix rice vinegar and 1 tsp white sugar in a small bowl. Toss in sliced cucumbers and set aside to pickle.",
        "Preheat oven broiler to High (550°F / 290°C).",
        "Place cubed salmon in a large bowl. Toss with avocado oil, tamari, brown sugar, garlic powder, ginger powder, sesame seeds, and togarashi (if using).",
        "Spread salmon on a rimmed baking sheet. Broil for 6-8 minutes until slightly browned and cooked through.",
        "Whisk together mayonnaise, sriracha, and lime juice in a small bowl to make the spicy mayo.",
        "Assemble bowls: Start with coconut rice, top with pickled cucumber and broiled salmon. Add sliced avocado and garnish with furikake and chives. Drizzle with spicy mayo and serve."
